	<text>
		<body>
			<pb n="1"/>
				<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>New York</placeName> <date>Dec. 21. 1850</date></p>
				<p>The <addressee>Revd. Isaac Leeser</addressee></p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Dr. Sir</p>
			<p rend="indent(2)">My absence from home for more than a<lb/> week has deferred the accomplishment of my promise<lb/> until this time.  I hasten to comply with the request<lb/> of your letter&#44; which I find on my return to <placeName>New York</placeName>.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">I was not aware of the publication of <persName>Mr. Pey&#45;<lb/>nado&#39;s</persName> letter in the Asmonean until informed by you.  How<lb/> it could have been published&#44; I cannot imagine un&#45;<lb/>less through the agency of some one into whose hands the<lb/> manuscript has fallen since the meeting of Synod&#8212;for<lb/> on examining my papers I find that it was not<lb/> returned to me as Stated Clerk&#44; by the committee &#38;<lb/> whom it and the numbers of the Occident were referred.<lb/>  I will make inquiry and if possible ascertain in<lb/> what was the manuscript got into the hands of the<lb/> publisher of the Asmonean.  Of one thing however<lb/> you may assure <persName>Mr. Peynado</persName>&#44; that you did faithfully<lb/> transmit his manuscript to me&#44; and that&#44; after it<lb/> had been in my possession for several months it<lb/> was duly laid before the Synod.  Until I read</p>
			<pb n="2"/>
				<p>your letter I certainly supposed that it had<lb/> been returned to me with the other documents&#44;<lb/> which are properly to be in my custody.  As early<lb/> as I can trace the matter&#44; and procure the mau&#45;<lb/>script&#44; I will communicate with you farther.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Meanwhile&#44; I am very respectfully</p>
			<p rend="indent(3)">Your obedt. &#38;c</p>
			<p rend="indent(3)"><persName role="author">John M Krebs</persName>.</p>
			<pb n="3"/>
				<p rend="align(center)">In the Synod of <placeName>New York</placeName>&#58;</p>
				<p rend="align(right)">At <placeName>New York</placeName>&#44; <date>Oct. 17<hi rend="sup">th</hi>. 1850</date>.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">The Committee to whom had been referred<lb/> certain papers communicated by the <persName>Revd. Isaac<lb/> Leeser</persName>&#44; from various sources&#44; noticing the Ad&#45;<lb/>dres to the Jews by the Synod last year&#44; made<lb/> a report which was adopted&#44; as follows&#44; viz</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">&#8220;Whereas the documents addressed to the<lb/> Synod and referred to this Committee are from<lb/> individual Israelites&#44; unauthorized to speak<lb/> for the Jewish Community within the bounds of<lb/> the Synod&#44; therefore&#44; Resolved that the committee<lb/> cannot recommend to the Synod to make<lb/> any official reply to the same.&#8221;</p>
			<p rend="indent(2)">Attest.</p>
			<p rend="indent(3)"><persName role="author">John M Krebs</persName></p>
			<p rend="indent(4)">Stated Clerk.</p>
		</body>
